WEBVTT

00:00.290 --> 00:08.199
Wow, Corbin, if you guys weren't blessed this morning by Corbin and the praise team, you weren't paying attention.

00:09.720 --> 00:12.844
We are so blessed to have him here.

00:14.726 --> 00:15.507
Thank you, Corbin.

00:15.547 --> 00:16.568
Thank you, praise team.

00:19.812 --> 00:29.362
Now, in the spirit of being a very good Big Ten sports fan, even though I'm a boilermaker at heart,

00:30.530 --> 00:39.363
I want to give my utmost congratulations to all of you IU fans out there in the crowd for a wonderful victory on Friday.

00:40.024 --> 00:42.508
And the best of luck to you next Monday.

00:42.788 --> 00:44.991
I know Brian, you can't believe I said it, can you?

00:45.392 --> 00:47.235
Can't believe those words came out of my mouth.

00:49.878 --> 00:57.810
I'm going to be preaching today in the continuation of the sermon series that Tim started last Sunday.

00:58.722 --> 01:03.028
called the generosity series.

01:03.048 --> 01:10.358
And for you that were here, Tim spoke about the first offerings ever recorded in the scripture.

01:11.739 --> 01:18.649
Genesis tells us that Cain and Abel both brought their offerings to present to the Lord.

01:20.371 --> 01:23.996
Tim taught us why Abel's offering was more pleasing to God.

01:25.017 --> 01:28.562
And it was because it was of the firstborn, the fat

01:28.674 --> 01:29.195
portion.

01:31.697 --> 01:33.018
It was about priority.

01:35.260 --> 01:39.164
You see, Abel trusted God with what came first.

01:41.667 --> 01:44.750
Abel's offering demonstrated his faith and trust in the Lord.

01:46.972 --> 01:57.362
And Genesis shows us that worship isn't just about what we give, but it's about how

01:58.018 --> 02:00.041
and why we give.

02:01.423 --> 02:07.230
First fruit's giving isn't as much about generosity as it is about faith.

02:08.372 --> 02:13.218
It says, God, I trust you with what comes next.

02:15.521 --> 02:19.747
And it's this faithfulness that God desires.

02:21.950 --> 02:25.234
Tim shared last week with you his first

02:25.986 --> 02:30.772
tithing story or his first giving as a young man when he came to faith.

02:31.913 --> 02:35.297
Now, pagan my stories are just a little bit different.

02:35.317 --> 02:36.919
You see, I grew up in the church.

02:37.499 --> 02:43.206
I grew up watching my grandfather and my father just tithe.

02:43.266 --> 02:44.908
That was just part of our life.

02:45.509 --> 02:47.992
And I'll be honest, it was pretty easy for pagan.

02:48.032 --> 02:51.256
When we got married, I was still in college.

02:51.516 --> 02:53.298
I was a sophomore at Ball State.

02:55.586 --> 02:56.587
I didn't have a job.

02:57.808 --> 03:05.817
Peggy was working full-time making a whopping minimum wage at the Hertz Car rental agency in Anderson, Indiana.

03:08.100 --> 03:13.906
We were living on $8,000 a year in 1984.

03:15.548 --> 03:20.974
Now, so when you think about it, $10,800 is nothing.

03:21.834 --> 03:25.138
I mean, in the whole scheme of things that didn't change our life,

03:25.442 --> 03:27.545
Didn't take a lot of faith for us to give.

03:28.827 --> 03:40.162
Then I graduate from college, get my degree in organic chemistry, and I get the best job that an organic chemist could have at the time in research with Eli Lilly.

03:41.404 --> 03:43.888
Sign that contract and I tell you I was set.

03:44.128 --> 03:50.136
I could not believe we were going to be making $24,000 a year.

03:50.437 --> 03:51.378
Where's it going to go?

03:51.906 --> 03:55.653
How in the world can the two of us spend $24,000 a year?

03:56.455 --> 03:58.839
So it was pretty simple to tie then too.

03:59.500 --> 04:03.468
She and I were both big fans of Larry Burkett.

04:03.668 --> 04:10.661
Now you youngsters have never heard of Larry Burkett, but he was the Dave Ramsey of my generation, okay?

04:11.663 --> 04:13.106
So it was pretty easy.

04:13.570 --> 04:14.732
We just budgeted.

04:14.812 --> 04:16.835
My wife is a wonderful budgeteer.

04:17.095 --> 04:19.979
If you know her, she's got the little green ledgers.

04:20.500 --> 04:24.025
I mean, she's in her joy when she's doing bookkeeping.

04:24.446 --> 04:28.672
So we had her little budget set up and we just based it on 90% of 24,000.

04:28.712 --> 04:29.273
It was simple.

04:29.533 --> 04:31.136
There was a confess.

04:31.256 --> 04:34.941
It didn't take a lot of faith for us to give.

04:37.345 --> 04:37.926
It really didn't.

04:39.308 --> 04:40.850
Then I left Lily.

04:41.602 --> 04:48.251
because I wanted to move back here and be around all you guys and started my business with Edward Jones.

04:49.312 --> 04:54.600
Now that's a little different because now I'm working 100% commission.

04:57.263 --> 05:04.613
I started every month going into the office and hit the computer screen and my commission screen says zero.

05:05.975 --> 05:11.122
That's when I learned what it truly meant to live by faith

05:11.810 --> 05:20.342
and to give by faith, to trust God with the first fruits, and to trust Him with what comes next.

05:22.424 --> 05:34.541
Now, I want to just stop right here and tell you my message today in Tim's message in this series is not a prosperity gospel message, okay?

05:35.282 --> 05:41.490
That's not what I'm going to be talking about today, not at all.

05:41.602 --> 05:43.565
I don't believe in prosperity gospel.

05:43.625 --> 05:44.866
I don't even want to go there.

05:45.367 --> 05:48.291
That's not where I want to go today.

05:48.311 --> 05:58.886
I want you to get the message that if we are faithful, if you are faithful to Him, He will be faithful to you.

06:00.808 --> 06:08.018
And we will receive the blessing that this song sings about today.

06:09.762 --> 06:16.350
And one of the reasons this song means so much to me, as Corbin mentioned, is it is directly from Scripture.

06:18.232 --> 06:24.739
Numbers chapter 6, verses 24 through 26.

06:27.883 --> 06:30.947
The Lord bless you and keep you.

06:32.629 --> 06:37.394
The Lord make His face shine on you and be gracious to you.

06:38.818 --> 06:43.645
The Lord turned his face toward you and give you peace.

06:43.665 --> 06:52.459
I want to start by giving you a little background, a little context of where this priestly blessing came from.

06:52.479 --> 06:59.610
See, God had just led through Moses the Israelites out of bondage in Egypt.

07:01.012 --> 07:04.978
They'd been in captivity and in a foreign land for years and years.

07:07.138 --> 07:09.021
Moses had taken him out to the desert.

07:09.101 --> 07:12.466
God had delivered the Ten Commandments to Moses.

07:12.747 --> 07:19.697
In other words, his law, his covenant, what he desired for his people to do, to be faithful to him.

07:21.700 --> 07:31.075
They had just finished building a tabernacle and they were beginning regular worship in the tabernacle in the wilderness.

07:33.038 --> 07:35.762
And Moses told Aaron,

07:36.706 --> 07:43.194
in all of his sons in offspring who were going to be the priest, the lineage of priests throughout history.

07:43.955 --> 07:45.817
This is the blessing.

07:46.438 --> 07:53.867
These are the words that I want you to deliver to the people when they're worshiping.

07:54.388 --> 08:06.162
After they have presented their sacrifices and their offerings before the altar, Aaron would give these words as a blessing.

08:06.498 --> 08:08.481
to those that were faithful.

08:13.208 --> 08:31.495
So essentially, if I could kind of sum up what God's desire was for His people, I think I can say it in this one word, to love the Lord your God and to serve Him with all your heart and with all your soul.

08:33.478 --> 08:36.402
That's what God is desiring from us.

08:38.402 --> 08:48.998
That's what it takes for us to be faithful to Him, to receive this blessing and to have Him put His name upon us.

08:50.981 --> 08:59.413
So let's break the blessing down verse by verse and see what it means to you and me today.

09:01.877 --> 09:07.826
Verse 24, the Lord bless you and keep you.

09:08.930 --> 09:14.797
See, when the Lord blesses you, He shows His favor to you.

09:15.678 --> 09:22.167
And He shows His favor by being abundant with everything that you need.

09:22.307 --> 09:26.392
He is your abundant source of all good things.

09:28.615 --> 09:34.662
And if you want to get deeper into just what that means, you can go to Deuteronomy chapter 28.

09:34.762 --> 09:37.746
It spells out

09:38.306 --> 09:39.707
how God will bless you.

09:39.727 --> 09:42.470
And just a few of them I'm gonna list here.

09:42.510 --> 09:47.636
The Lord your God will set you high above all the nations on earth.

09:48.897 --> 09:51.440
The fruit of your womb will be blessed.

09:51.460 --> 09:53.182
In other words, your children.

09:54.683 --> 09:57.126
The crops of your land will be blessed.

09:58.627 --> 10:01.470
The young of your livestock will be blessed.

10:01.490 --> 10:05.074
Your basket and your kneading trough will be blessed.

10:05.506 --> 10:10.193
Your barns and everything you put your hand to will be blessed.

10:11.115 --> 10:18.006
Essentially, all you do will be blessed, but that's not all.

10:20.429 --> 10:24.897
Verse 24 goes on to say, he will also keep you.

10:25.998 --> 10:29.864
Now the Hebrew word for this is Shemar.

10:31.988 --> 10:33.490
And Shemar means,

10:35.106 --> 10:37.429
to guard and to protect.

10:38.590 --> 10:46.580
And what it literally means is that he will place a hedge of protection around you and your family.

10:49.423 --> 10:50.705
What a perfect father.

10:55.931 --> 11:01.358
Not only does he provide for us, but he also protects us.

11:03.400 --> 11:05.042
Let's move on to verse 25.

11:07.682 --> 11:13.649
The Lord make His face shine on you and be gracious to you.

11:15.852 --> 11:22.080
When God makes His face shine on you, He's looking upon you with favor.

11:23.641 --> 11:29.529
And it suggests that God looks at us and smiles.

11:30.650 --> 11:31.972
Isn't that an awesome picture?

11:34.955 --> 11:37.298
I think of how I feel

11:38.274 --> 11:53.955
When I look at my children and my grandchildren, trust me, there was no better feeling than when I'm sitting there at my son's house on Christmas Day.

11:55.617 --> 11:57.459
And I've got all my family around me.

11:59.682 --> 12:03.167
And these little kids are running around playing with each other.

12:03.247 --> 12:05.650
I mean, they just, it's just precious.

12:07.138 --> 12:12.325
And I just sat there and smiled.

12:12.345 --> 12:16.771
That's how God feels when He looks upon us.

12:17.232 --> 12:22.939
When we are faithful to Him, He looks down on us and smiles.

12:31.291 --> 12:36.658
Well, verse 25 ends with Him being gracious to us.

12:38.146 --> 12:45.358
Because God is gracious, we are the recipients of His compassion and steadfast love.

12:46.981 --> 12:52.451
One of my favorite verses demonstrates this, and it's Romans 5-8.

12:52.611 --> 13:00.585
And I have to tell a little story about this verse because it's kind of funny.

13:01.927 --> 13:03.730
Back when I was a younger man,

13:04.514 --> 13:10.460
Maybe in my 30s, instead of my 60s, I played a lot of ball.

13:10.940 --> 13:12.542
Played a lot of softball.

13:13.122 --> 13:18.348
And we had three teams here at this church in a league.

13:18.408 --> 13:20.209
And I played on the old man's league.

13:20.310 --> 13:21.491
We were called Omega.

13:22.251 --> 13:23.873
We had the Alpha and the Omega.

13:24.313 --> 13:25.655
Alpha was the young kids.

13:26.576 --> 13:28.778
Omega were the old men.

13:29.018 --> 13:31.000
And then there was Epsilon in there also.

13:31.400 --> 13:33.042
But anyhow, our team cap

13:34.434 --> 13:36.136
We all wore the same ball cap.

13:36.837 --> 13:39.721
We had jerseys and a team cap and it had a cross on it.

13:40.382 --> 13:41.984
It was called the cross cap.

13:42.585 --> 13:43.426
Pretty simple, right?

13:43.987 --> 13:49.514
But on the side, right here on the side above our ears was Romans 5, 8.

13:51.937 --> 13:55.021
One of my good friends, his wife challenged him one day.

13:55.982 --> 13:59.447
He goes, so, what's Romans 5, 8?

14:00.588 --> 14:01.810
What's the scripture?

14:02.882 --> 14:07.229
and he was caught like a deer in the head like, I don't know.

14:07.870 --> 14:12.216
Well, if you're going to be wearing that on your head, you darn well should know what it means.

14:13.719 --> 14:26.118
And what Romans 5, 8 says is that God demonstrates his love for us in this, that while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.

14:30.364 --> 14:31.666
He accepts us.

14:33.218 --> 14:34.840
while we are yet sinners.

14:37.584 --> 14:46.356
He redeems this by his forgiveness and he keeps redeeming us through his faithful presence and power.

14:49.360 --> 14:52.744
I want to move on to the final part of this blessing, verse 26.

14:55.408 --> 14:59.794
The Lord, turn his face toward you and give you peace.

15:02.306 --> 15:09.857
When the Lord turns his face toward us, he's giving us his full attention.

15:10.538 --> 15:11.519
No distractions.

15:12.280 --> 15:13.842
He's not looking left or right.

15:15.565 --> 15:21.393
He's looking right into our eyes and giving us his full attention.

15:23.676 --> 15:24.818
No distractions.

15:26.818 --> 15:29.583
And it reminds me of when I'm around my grandkids.

15:29.963 --> 15:33.910
Again, I'm sorry if I'm bringing them up too much, but they're important in my life.

15:36.755 --> 15:38.778
But you're trying to get a message across to them.

15:41.422 --> 15:49.496
And like any five-year-old, eight-year-old, three-year-old, you name it, their little minds are going, here, here, here, here, here, here, here.

15:50.117 --> 15:53.202
And I'm trying to get their attention, and it's like,

15:53.346 --> 15:55.228
Look me in the eyes.

15:55.368 --> 16:02.074
And sometimes I have to grab their face and say, look me in the eyes and listen.

16:03.976 --> 16:05.678
Well, see, that's what God does to us.

16:06.418 --> 16:07.940
He loves us so much.

16:07.980 --> 16:09.801
There are no distractions.

16:10.262 --> 16:15.687
He is looking directly at us, right in our eyes.

16:15.767 --> 16:23.314
And because of this, we can live our lives in this messed up

16:23.650 --> 16:32.764
screwed up world that we're in today and we can look into his eyes and we can find peace.

16:36.230 --> 16:39.294
This is the blessing that God wants to bestow on us.

16:43.621 --> 16:45.945
But you know, we have to want to receive it, don't we?

16:47.587 --> 16:51.794
He wants to bestow it, but we have to be willing to receive it.

16:54.434 --> 16:59.401
And we also need to be willing to pass it on.

17:02.665 --> 17:07.471
This is what the second part of the blessing song is all about.

17:10.516 --> 17:24.274
May his favor be upon you and a thousand generations in your family and your children and their children.

17:24.834 --> 17:25.955
and their children.

17:29.859 --> 17:34.565
This is the part of the song where I have to stop because I just break down and weep.

17:34.625 --> 17:37.808
I can't continue to sing at this part.

17:40.371 --> 17:50.642
You see, I stand here as a recipient of that blessing.

17:53.698 --> 18:01.046
because of how my grandfather and my father lived their lives.

18:07.293 --> 18:14.420
I could not have asked for a better spiritual ancestry than what I was given.

18:17.844 --> 18:23.250
My grandpa Eldon lived out his faithfulness every day of his life.

18:24.866 --> 18:26.948
I grew up working on the farm with him.

18:27.008 --> 18:32.595
So I saw him every day in good situations and in bad situations.

18:32.695 --> 18:38.301
And he didn't just live a faithful life here at church when the doors were open.

18:39.602 --> 18:41.144
He lived it every day.

18:46.450 --> 18:53.938
I also had the privilege of serving here as an elder at the same time that he was an elder.

18:57.154 --> 19:09.486
And it was pretty incredible to watch him with his calm wisdom as he went about trying to lead our church and the way that we should go.

19:13.030 --> 19:25.682
Because of his faithfulness, his son, my dad followed in his footsteps and he raised us six kids

19:26.178 --> 19:31.623
to be just as strong in our faith.

19:31.643 --> 19:34.646
Some of you know Dad's story, some of you don't.

19:37.028 --> 19:45.396
Again, his story is not one that someone that was up here to preach a prosperity gospel would use.

19:47.979 --> 19:55.826
My dad, at age 34, lost his wife and my mom,

19:57.698 --> 19:58.419
sudden death.

19:59.140 --> 20:07.712
And here he is with four ornery kids, 12 and under and a farm to run all by himself.

20:10.176 --> 20:15.664
Fortunately, he was blessed to be my current mom and had two more children.

20:17.727 --> 20:22.994
But then at age 49, he lost everything he worked for.

20:26.018 --> 20:28.101
lost his farm, lost all of his land.

20:28.882 --> 20:34.570
Everything he owned, he watched to be sold off in a sheriff's auction.

20:38.295 --> 20:45.806
He had every reason to walk away from faith and to say, God, this is not what I signed up for.

20:45.846 --> 20:49.491
I've done everything I can.

20:49.551 --> 20:54.738
I've lived my life and this is what I get.

20:57.474 --> 21:02.802
You see, according to the world's standards, my dad is not prosperous.

21:06.668 --> 21:20.850
But according to the things of eternal importance, faith, family, friends, my dad is the richest man in America.

21:26.498 --> 21:36.491
If you would have stepped foot in my brother's barn in the middle of December when we had the big Cayley Christmas, and when everyone's there, there's close to 50 of us.

21:38.734 --> 21:42.960
And I just love sitting there and watching my dad sit back in his chair.

21:43.741 --> 21:47.886
He doesn't say much, but he just looks around and smiles.

21:49.429 --> 21:53.554
He knows he's the richest man in America.

21:55.906 --> 22:01.913
He has been blessed, not by the world's standards, but by God's standards.

22:05.036 --> 22:12.464
My grandpa Eldon was my spiritual hero, so was and is.

22:15.808 --> 22:16.269
My dad.

22:20.393 --> 22:24.818
My hope is that someday my grandchildren will look to me

22:25.538 --> 22:27.281
as their spiritual hero.

22:29.584 --> 22:32.188
In the same way I looked up to Grandpa Elden and my dad.

22:32.969 --> 22:47.130
I can't think of any better legacy to leave this world and receive my reward than to have my grandchildren and my children feel about me the way I do about dad and grandpa.

22:48.973 --> 22:52.498
And even to this day, one of the greatest blessings I get each week

22:53.442 --> 23:04.101
is standing next to my dad during worship service and listening to his 86-year-old voice, spelled out these worship songs.

23:04.221 --> 23:11.614
I guarantee if anyone was sitting around him this morning, they would have heard him singing just as loud as anyone else.

23:14.399 --> 23:18.706
And then on that same day, being able to see my son,

23:20.418 --> 23:27.168
and grandchildren, and today my daughters here also, they normally attend a church in Fort Wayne, but she's here today.

23:27.209 --> 23:30.794
There's no greater blessing than that.

23:33.358 --> 23:45.937
I hope that each and every one of you has been blessed with faithful examples like I've been blessed with through my father and through my grandfather.

23:46.859 --> 23:48.882
I hope you have someone in your family

23:49.346 --> 23:51.088
That is your spiritual hero.

23:53.972 --> 23:58.278
And if you don't, then be that person.

24:00.822 --> 24:04.887
Live your life in a way that makes a difference.

24:08.833 --> 24:13.679
Become the superhero of faith for your family.

24:15.902 --> 24:18.706
So my challenge to you is this, live in a way

24:18.786 --> 24:32.159
that you not only receive the blessing, but also allow that blessing to be passed down to your children and their children to a thousand generations.

24:34.902 --> 24:38.265
Let me wrap it up by reciting the blessing one more time for you.

24:40.427 --> 24:43.270
The Lord bless you and keep you.

24:45.252 --> 24:47.474
The Lord make His face shine on you.

24:48.706 --> 24:50.989
and be gracious to you.

24:52.992 --> 24:58.561
The Lord turn his face toward you and give you peace.

25:01.706 --> 25:07.735
This is a powerful and generous blessing that he has bestowed upon us.

25:09.638 --> 25:17.810
However, the greatest blessing is that our Heavenly Father sent his one

25:17.954 --> 25:27.568
and only Son to become flesh and to die for the forgiveness of our sins.

25:30.773 --> 25:41.529
I hope that we never lose our fascination with that, with the fact that Almighty God emptied Himself and took on the form of a man.

25:43.472 --> 25:47.538
Everything else is so ridiculous compared

25:48.034 --> 25:59.931
to this one great truth of God, becoming man, dying on a cross for all of our sins and rising from the dead.

26:01.914 --> 26:12.088
The creator of the universe loved us so much that he emptied himself of all of his glory, and he comes down to pursue us.

26:13.831 --> 26:15.954
That's the good news.

26:19.042 --> 26:27.876
I hope and pray that each and every one of you have realized this and have accepted him as your Lord and Savior.

26:31.141 --> 26:38.753
If you've not reached that decision yet and you'd like to discuss it further, I welcome you to come up at the end of the service.

26:38.913 --> 26:39.855
I will be down here.

26:39.955 --> 26:44.322
I would love to have that conversation with you about that.

26:46.345 --> 26:47.186
Or maybe

26:47.746 --> 26:58.939
You just would like to take that next level, that next step of faith to become the superhero of faith for your family.

26:59.880 --> 27:03.003
To step your spiritual walk up just one more notch.

27:03.964 --> 27:05.206
Again, I'll be down here.

27:05.246 --> 27:08.369
I'd love to talk to you about taking that step also.

27:10.492 --> 27:15.858
And I hope as you came in that each one of you picked up a communion packet,

27:21.026 --> 27:49.056
I'm going to ask that each of you take a moment and just consider the amazing fact that we just discussed, that God Almighty, the creator of the universe sent his one and only son to come down to this earth and pursue us, to lay his life down, to die on the cross for my sin and for your sin.

27:50.177 --> 27:50.898
Let's take a moment.

28:48.706 --> 29:08.914
that night when he was in the upper room with his disciples about to lay down his life he took the bread and said take and eat for this is my body which is broken for you

29:18.242 --> 29:33.558
took the cup and said, this is my blood that is poured out for you.

29:33.578 --> 29:44.850
Our Heavenly Father, we just thank You so much for coming down, taking on flesh, becoming

29:47.522 --> 29:56.351
pursuing us, for laying your life down, for the forgiveness of my sin.

30:00.476 --> 30:07.463
Lord, thank you for blessing us beyond what we deserve.

30:07.483 --> 30:17.394
Lord, I pray that as we go out this week, that we be salt and light in an example for others to see how you have blessed.

30:18.018 --> 30:21.138
lives and it's in your name that I pray.

